<?php die('Unauthorized access.'); ?>a:39:{s:2:"id";s:2:"12";s:4:"type";s:8:"document";s:11:"contentType";s:9:"text/html";s:9:"pagetitle";s:21:"Christian Stewardship";s:9:"longtitle";s:21:"Christian Stewardship";s:11:"description";s:0:"";s:5:"alias";s:11:"stewardship";s:15:"link_attributes";s:0:"";s:9:"published";s:1:"1";s:8:"pub_date";s:1:"0";s:10:"unpub_date";s:1:"0";s:6:"parent";s:1:"4";s:8:"isfolder";s:1:"0";s:9:"introtext";s:0:"";s:7:"content";s:2811:"<p>
Christian Stewardship is the believer's recognition that all one has belongs  to God.&nbsp; As a believer, we know that the grace of God is a free and  unmerited gift, therefore, we rest upon this grace relationship with God.&nbsp;  This relationship is understood in light of believers first giving themselves to  God in unqualified dedication (2 Cor. 8:5).&nbsp; A true commitment of self to  God includes all that one is and has; life, time, strength, ability, ideals, and  property (1 Cor. 6:20; 7:23; 1 Peter 1:18, 19).
</p>
<p>
One of the premier examples of Christian Stewardship is tithing.&nbsp; It is  an expression of devotion from the giver and recognition of God's sovereignty.
</p>
<p>
The Bible admonishes us that the purpose of tithing is to teach you always to  put God first in your lives.&nbsp; (Deut. 14:23 LB).&nbsp; God will sustain  grace-giving with limitless temporal resources (2 Cor. 9:8-10).
</p>
<p>
Mt. Zion is committed to the TITHING MODEL and believes it demonstrates  responsible stewardship.&nbsp; We take the commands of our Lord seriously.&nbsp;  When Jesus tells us to go into all the world and spread the Gospel, we believe  that our giving confirms our love of Christ and our recognition of His  sovereignty.&nbsp; He is our provider and is worthy of all praise and  glory.&nbsp; Our TITHE is an expression of our love!!
</p>
<p>
&nbsp; 
</p>
<h2>Worship in Giving Litany</h2>
<p>
<img alt="Praying Hands" class="left" height="226" src="assets/images/praying_hands.jpg" title="Praying Hands" width="160" />Honor the Lord with thy substance and with the first fruits of all thine increase 
</p>
<p>
Proverbs 3:9
</p>
<p>
&nbsp;
</p>
<p>
So shall thy barns be filled with plenty, and they presses shall burst out with new wine. 
</p>
<p>
Proverbs 3:10
</p>
<p>
&nbsp;
</p>
<p>
Upon the first day of the week let everyone of you lay by Him in store, as God hath prospered him, that there be no gatherings when I come.
</p>
<p>
1 Corinthians 16:2
</p>
<p>
&nbsp;
</p>
<p>
And all the tithes of the land, whether of the seed of the land, or the fruit of the trees, it is the Lord's: it is holy unto the Lord
</p>
<p>
Leviticus 27:30
</p>
<p>
Will a man rob God?  Yet ye have robbed me.  But ye say, wherein have we robbed thee?  In tithes and offerings.
</p>
<p>
Malachi 3:8
</p>
<p>
Bring ye all the tithes unto the storehouse, that there may be meat in mine house, and prove me now herewith, saith the Lord of hosts, if I will not open you the windows of heaven, and pour you out a blessing that there shall not be room enough to receive it.
</p>
<p>
Malachi 3:10
</p>
